{{+add+}} Add a "Why This Is Hard" callout:
{{+**Why This Is Hard:** Answer (D) trips up many students because it requires a hypothetical inference: "if digitalization technology were made even easier to use." The passage supports this -- it says enforcement is hard partly because copying is a "relatively simple process," so making it simpler would logically increase violations. Answer (C) is the correct choice because it treats an open question (whether a revised law will prohibit secondary copies) as a settled fact. The passage explicitly frames this as an unresolved question, not a conclusion.+}}


